[[File:Nemanjić dynasty Belgrade Armorial II.jpg|thumb|<center>[[Nemanjić dynasty]]]]
The '''Belgrade Armorial II''' ({{lang-sr|Beogradski grbovnik II/Београдски грбовник II}}) is the name given to an [[armorial]] compiled between 1600 and 1620, as a copy of [[Korenić-Neorić Armorial|Petar Ohmućević's armorial]] which is dated to {{circa}} 1590. It was bought by Russian historian [[Alexander Soloviev (historian)|Alexander Soloviev]] in 1936, and is today held at the [[Museum of Applied Arts (Belgrade)|Museum of Applied Art]] in [[Belgrade]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Rudić |first=Srđan |title=Vlastela ilirskog grbovnika |year=2006 |publisher=Istorijski institut |location=Beograd |isbn=86-7743-055-5 |pages=65}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|editor-last=Zorić |editor-first=Ivanka |title=Museum of Applied Art : 1950–2005  |url=http://www.mpu.rs/srpski/izdavacka_delatnost/fajlovi/Museum%20of%20Applied%20Art%201950%20-%202005.pdf |year=2010 |publisher=Museum of Applied Art |location=Belgrade |isbn=978-86-7415-137-2 |pages=128-129}}</ref> It is among the oldest, and finest of the Illyrian Armorials. Its origin remain unknown.<ref>{{cite book|title=Odbrana: magazin Ministarstva odbrane SCG.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=g2UpAQAAIAAJ|year=2007|publisher=Novinsko-izdavački centar "Vojska,"|quote=Београдски грбовник II спада мег)у HajcTapnje, а сигурно и меЬу Hajnenme илирске збирке грбова. Како je настао, у Koje сврхе, ко га je преписивао и дописивао током векова, прича je слична истори Ском трилеру - иза ког je, а то je ...}}</ref>

