{{Same-sex marriage map South America|align=left}}
'''Lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender''' ([[LGBT]]) people in [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]], Brazil enjoy many of the same legal protections available to non-LGBT people. Homosexuality is legal in the state.

==Same-sex marriage==
In 2004, the first case of recognition of [[same-sex union]]s in Brazil occurred with a binational [[English people|Englishman]] and a [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]]. This [[legal precedent]] encouraged other couples to marry around the country. At the time of the ceremony, in the form of [[common-law marriage]], this was a status that, until then, was only granted to opposite-sex couples. The couple had lived together for fourteen years, in the Brazilian city of [[Curitiba]].<ref>[http://www.jornalcomunicacao.ufpr.br/node/7987 The first registered same-sex union in a Brazilian notary public] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120317055941/http://www.jornalcomunicacao.ufpr.br/node/7987 |date=2012-03-17 }} {{pt icon}}</ref>

On 26 March 2013, the Corregedor Geral de Justiça of Paraná ruled that [[same-sex marriage]] and conversion of the stable unions to marriage should be possible using the normal marriage procedures. <ref>[http://www.parana-online.com.br/editoria/cidades/news/660511/?noticia=CASAMENTO+GAY+ESTA+VALENDO+EM+TODO+O+PARANA] {{pt icon}}</ref>

==LGBT adoption==
'''May 14, 2009''' − a gay couple was the first to win in court the right of [[adoption]] in the Brazilian State of [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]]. A decision of the 2nd Court of Childhood, Youth and Adoption, changed the life of a homosexual couple who live in [[Curitiba]]. Two years previously, the gay couple had attempted to adopt a child. They had their request granted by a judge who ruled that the couple were living in a stable and affectionate union, and were able to raise a child of either sex and age in a healthy environment.<ref>[http://www.parana-online.com.br/editoria/cidades/news/372528/ Same-sex adoption in Paraná {{pt icon}}]</ref>

'''October 27, 2010''' − the Justice of the city of [[Cascavel]], [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]], authorized the adoption of an eight-year-old child with [[cerebral palsy]] by a [[Same-sex couple|gay couple]] who had been living together for twelve years. The authorization is irreversible, according to Judge Sergio Luiz Kreuz, who granted the application for adoption based on the decision of the Superior Court of Justice.<ref>[http://odia.terra.com.br/portal/brasil/html/2010/10/justica_autoriza_casal_gay_a_adotar_crianca_deficiente_no_parana_120243.html Gay couple adoption in Paraná {{pt icon}}]</ref>

'''September 16, 2011''' - the Justice of the city of [[Maringá]], [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]] authorized the adoption of two children by a lesbian couple.<ref>[http://www.direitohomoafetivo.com.br/uploads_jurisprudencia/%31%31%33%35%2E%70%64%66 Lesbian couple adoption in Paraná {{pt icon}}]</ref>

