{{Oceania-party-stub}}

The '''Party of the Third Age''' ({{lang-lb|Partei vum 3. Alter}}, {{lang-fr|Parti du Troisième Âge}}) was a [[political party]] in [[Luxembourg]].  It contested the [[Luxembourg legislative election, 1999|1999 election]] to the [[Chamber of Deputies of Luxembourg|Chamber of Deputies]], but has since disbanded.

Its party platform was dedicated to [[pensioner]]s' issues, and its name is a reference to its core constituency.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.europeanvoice.com/archive/article.asp?id=9150 |title=Little Luxembourg makes a big impact |accessdate= |last= |first= |date=3 June 1999 |publisher=[[European Voice]] }}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>  In its only legislative election in which it stood candidates, in [[Luxembourgian legislative election, 1999|1999]], it contested only the [[Circonscription Sud (Luxembourg)|Sud]] constituency, in which it came eighth and last, with 0.4% of the vote.  It folded soon afterwards.

